AbuseIPDB Checker is an OPNsense plugin that monitors external IPs 
attempting to connect to your LAN subnets and checks them against 
the AbuseIPDB reputation database.

Features:
* Monitor external IPs targeting your LAN subnets
* Check suspicious IPs against AbuseIPDB's reputation database
* Include connection port information in alerts
* Configurable protocol filtering
* Option to focus only on allowed connections
* Daily API check limits to manage usage
* Weekly IP rechecking to avoid duplicate lookups
* Email notifications for potential threats

WWW: https://github.com/yourusername/opnsense-abuseipdb-plugin